Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola, has said the ruling All Progressives Congress remains united and intact in the state, urging its members and the electorate to be resolute in the task of ensuring his re-election. The governor also told members of the party to employ a door-to-door strategy and make the electorate realise why his administration should be given a second term in office. on Sunday in Osogbo during an engagement meeting organised by the State’s Civic Engagement Centre with Osun State Conference of Artists, Designers, House and Spraying Painters. Represented by his Special Adviser on Civic Engagement, Mr Olatunbosun Oyintiloye, the governor also urged APC members to educate the populace on the need for stability, sustainability and continuity of his people’s oriented style of governance. A statement signed by Oyintiloye quoting Oyetola partly read, “APC is still intact and indivisible in Osun. Don’t be agitated, but remain resolute, unflinching and committed to the task ahead. The mission is achievable. “Continue to educate the populace on the need for stability, sustainability and continuity of this people’s oriented style of governance. “As the election is approaching, we ask our members at all levels to employ door-to-door strategy to remind the electorate why our administration should be given a second chance to complete its developmental agenda for the state.” In his remarks, the chairman of the association, Siyanbola Shaeeb, assured that the group would support Oyetola’s re-election bid.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com